            "penne carbonara": `Ingredients:
                350g penne pasta
                150g pancetta or bacon, diced
                3 large eggs
                1 cup grated Parmesan cheese
                2 cloves garlic, minced
                Salt and black pepper to taste
                Fresh parsley for garnish (optional)
                Instructions:
                Cook penne pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
                In a skillet, cook diced pancetta or bacon until crispy. Remove from heat and drain excess fat.
                In a bowl, whisk together eggs, grated Parmesan cheese, minced garlic, salt, and black pepper.
                Add cooked pasta to the skillet with the pancetta/bacon. Pour the egg mixture over the pasta and toss quickly to coat.
                The residual heat from the pasta will cook the eggs and melt the cheese, creating a creamy sauce. If the sauce is too thick, add a splash of pasta cooking water.
                Serve immediately, garnished with fresh parsley if desired.`,
                "pizza diavola": `Ingredients:
        1 pre-made pizza dough
        1/2 cup pizza sauce
        1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
        100g spicy salami or pepperoni, thinly sliced
        1-2 red chili peppers, thinly sliced
        Fresh basil leaves for garnish
        Olive oil for drizzling
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Instructions:
        Preheat your oven to the highest temperature (usually around 475°F or 245°C).
        Roll out the pizza dough on a floured surface to your desired thickness.
        Transfer the dough to a pizza stone or baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
        Spread pizza sauce evenly over the dough, leaving a small border around the edges.
        Sprinkle shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
        Arrange slices of spicy salami or pepperoni on top of the cheese.
        Scatter thinly sliced red chili peppers over the pizza.
        Season with salt and black pepper to taste, and drizzle with olive oil.
        Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly.
        Remove from the oven, garnish with fresh basil leaves, slice, and serve hot.`,
    "vepřo knedlo zelo": `Ingredients:
        1 kg pork shoulder or pork loin
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        1 onion, peeled and halved
        2 carrots, peeled and chopped into large chunks
        2 celery stalks, chopped into large chunks
        2 bay leaves
        6-8 peppercorns
        Water
        500g sauerkraut
        1 tbsp vegetable oil
        1 tbsp sugar
        1 tbsp flour
        2-3 slices of bread (preferably Czech bread dumplings or rolls)
        Instructions:
        Season the pork shoulder or loin generously with salt and black pepper on all sides.
        In a large pot, place the seasoned pork, onion halves, carrots, celery, bay leaves, and peppercorns.
        Add enough water to cover the pork and vegetables. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, then reduce the heat to low and simmer gently for about 2-3 hours, or until the pork is tender.
        While the pork is cooking, prepare the sauerkraut. Heat vegetable oil in a separate pot over medium heat. Add the sauerkraut and sugar, and cook for about 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauerkraut is tender and slightly caramelized.
        Once the pork is cooked, remove it from the pot and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.
        In a small saucepan, prepare the gravy. Heat the vegetable oil over medium heat, then add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until it turns golden brown.
        Gradually whisk in some of the cooking liquid from the pork until the gravy reaches your desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
        Serve the sliced pork with sauerkraut, bread dumplings or rolls, and gravy on the side.`,
