    "beef ribeye steak": `Ingredients:
        2 ribeye steaks, about 1 inch thick
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Olive oil or butter
        Optional: minced garlic, fresh herbs (such as rosemary or thyme)
        Instructions:
        Take the ribeye steaks out of the refrigerator and let them sit at room temperature for about 30 minutes before cooking. This helps them cook more evenly.
        Preheat your grill or grill pan to high heat.
        Pat the steaks dry with paper towels to remove any excess moisture. Season both sides generously with salt and black pepper.
        If desired, rub minced garlic or fresh herbs onto the steaks for extra flavor.
        Drizzle olive oil or melt butter over the steaks to help prevent sticking and add flavor.
        Place the steaks on the hot grill or grill pan. Cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side for medium-rare doneness, or adjust the cooking time to your desired level of doneness.
        Use a meat thermometer to check the internal temperature of the steaks. For medium-rare, it should read around 130-135°F (54-57°C).
        Once cooked to your liking, remove the steaks from the grill and let them rest for a few minutes before slicing. This allows the juices to redistribute and ensures a juicy steak.
        Slice the ribeye steaks against the grain and serve immediately with your favorite side dishes.`,
    "guláš": `Ingredients:
        1 kg beef chuck or stew meat, cut into bite-sized pieces
        2 onions, finely chopped
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        2 tbsp sweet paprika
        1 tsp caraway seeds
        2 bay leaves
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        2 tbsp tomato paste
        2 cups beef broth or water
        2 tbsp vegetable oil
        Optional: red wine or beer for deglazing
        Instructions:
        Heat vegetable oil in a large pot or Dutch oven over medium heat. Add the chopped onions and cook until softened and translucent.
        Add the minced garlic, sweet paprika, and caraway seeds to the pot. Cook for another minute, stirring constantly, until fragrant.
        Add the beef pieces to the pot and season with salt and black pepper. Cook until the meat is browned on all sides.
        If using, deglaze the pot with a splash of red wine or beer, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pot for extra flavor.
        Stir in the tomato paste until well combined with the meat and onions.
        Add the bay leaves and enough beef broth or water to cover the meat by about an inch.
        Bring the mixture to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low and cover the pot. Let the guláš simmer gently for 2-3 hours, or until the meat is tender and the flavors have melded together.
        Taste and adjust the seasoning if necessary. Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley if desired, and with bread or dumplings on the side. Enjoy your comforting and hearty guláš!`,
    "spaghetti arrabiata": `Ingredients:
        300g spaghetti
        2 tbsp olive oil
        4 cloves garlic, minced
        1-2 red chili peppers, thinly sliced (adjust according to spice preference)
        1 can (400g) diced tomatoes
        1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Grated Parmesan cheese for serving (optional)
        Instructions:
        Cook the spaghetti in a large pot of salted boiling water according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
        In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add minced garlic and sliced red chili peppers. Cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly, until fragrant.
        Add the diced tomatoes to the skillet, including their juices. Bring to a simmer and cook for about 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has slightly thickened.
        Season the sauce with salt and black pepper to taste. Add chopped fresh parsley and stir to combine.
        Add the cooked spaghetti to the skillet with the arrabiata sauce. Toss well to coat the spaghetti evenly with the sauce.
        Serve hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese if desired. Enjoy your spicy and flavorful Spaghetti Arrabiata!`,
    "tomato soup": `Ingredients:
        2 tbsp olive oil
        1 onion, chopped
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        2 cans (800g total) diced tomatoes
        2 cups vegetable broth
        1 tsp dried basil
        1/2 tsp dried oregano
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        1/4 cup heavy cream (optional)
        Fresh basil leaves for garnish (optional)
        Instructions:
        Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add chopped onion and minced garlic. Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onion is soft and translucent.
        Add diced tomatoes (including their juices) to the pot. Stir in vegetable broth, dried basil, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper.
        Bring the soup to a simmer. Reduce the heat to low, cover the pot, and let it simmer for about 15-20 minutes to allow the flavors to meld together.
        Use an immersion blender or transfer the soup to a blender in batches to puree until smooth.
        If using, stir in the heavy cream to add creaminess to the soup. Adjust seasoning if necessary.
        Serve hot, garnished with fresh basil leaves if desired. Enjoy your comforting and delicious Tomato Soup!`,
    "benedict egg": `Ingredients:
        4 large eggs
        2 English muffins, split and toasted
        4 slices Canadian bacon or ham
        Hollandaise sauce (see recipe below)
        Chopped fresh chives or parsley for garnish (optional)
        Hollandaise Sauce Ingredients:
        3 large egg yolks
        1 tbsp lemon juice
        1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted
        Pinch of cayenne pepper
        Pinch of salt
        Instructions:
        Prepare the Hollandaise sauce: In a heatproof bowl, whisk together egg yolks and lemon juice until smooth.
        Place the bowl over a pot of simmering water (double boiler) and continue whisking constantly until the mixture thickens, about 2-3 minutes.
        Slowly drizzle in the melted butter while whisking continuously until the sauce is smooth and thickened. Be careful not to scramble the eggs.
        Remove the bowl from heat and season the Hollandaise sauce with cayenne pepper and salt. Keep warm while you prepare the rest of the dish.
        Poach the eggs: Bring a pot of water to a gentle simmer. Crack each egg into a small bowl or ramekin. Create a gentle whirlpool in the water and carefully slide the eggs into the center of the whirlpool. Cook for 3-4 minutes for soft poached eggs.
        While the eggs are poaching, place a slice of Canadian bacon or ham on each toasted English muffin half.
        Once the eggs are poached, carefully remove them from the water using a slotted spoon and place them on top of the Canadian bacon or ham.
        Spoon Hollandaise sauce generously over each egg. Garnish with chopped fresh chives or parsley if desired.
        Serve immediately and enjoy your delicious Eggs Benedict!`,
    "chicken kebab": `Ingredients:
        500g boneless, skinless chicken breasts or thighs, cut into bite-sized pieces
        1/4 cup Greek yogurt
        2 tbsp olive oil
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        1 tsp paprika
        1 tsp ground cumin
        1/2 tsp ground coriander
        1/2 tsp ground turmeric
        1/2 tsp ground cinnamon
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Wooden or metal skewers
        Optional: lemon wedges, chopped fresh parsley for serving
        Instructions:
        In a bowl, combine Greek yogurt, olive oil, minced garlic, paprika, cumin, coriander, turmeric, cinnamon, salt, and black pepper. Mix well to combine.
        Add the chicken pieces to the marinade and toss until evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or overnight for best results.
        If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for about 30 minutes to prevent burning.
        Preheat your grill or grill pan to medium-high heat.
        Thread the marinated chicken pieces onto the skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.
        Grill the chicken kebabs for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and charred on the edges.
        Once cooked, remove the kebabs from the grill and let them rest for a few minutes.
        Serve the chicken kebabs hot, garnished with lemon wedges and chopped fresh parsley if desired. Enjoy your flavorful and juicy Chicken Kebabs!`,
    "sushi maki": `Ingredients:
        2 cups sushi rice
        4 nori (seaweed) sheets
        Assorted fillings (e.g., cucumber, avocado, crab sticks, smoked salmon, tuna, etc.)
        Soy sauce, for serving
        Wasabi, for serving
        Pickled ginger, for serving
        Bamboo sushi rolling mat
        Plastic wrap (optional)
        Instructions:
        Cook sushi rice according to package instructions. Once cooked, let it cool to room temperature.
        Place a nori sheet on top of the bamboo sushi rolling mat. If desired, place a piece of plastic wrap on top of the nori sheet to prevent sticking.
        Spread a thin layer of sushi rice evenly over the nori sheet, leaving about 1 inch of space at the top edge.
        Arrange your desired fillings horizontally across the center of the rice-covered nori sheet.
        Using the bamboo sushi rolling mat, carefully roll the nori sheet over the fillings, applying gentle pressure to shape the roll. Continue rolling until the entire nori sheet is rolled up.
        Moisten the top edge of the nori sheet with a bit of water to seal the roll.
        Using a sharp knife, slice the sushi roll into individual pieces, about 1 inch thick.
        Repeat the process with the remaining nori sheets and fillings.
        Serve the sushi maki with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger on the side. Enjoy your homemade sushi maki!`,
    "chicken steak with potatoes": `Ingrecients:
        4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts
        4 large potatoes, peeled and cut into wedges
        2 tbsp olive oil
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        1 tsp paprika
        1 tsp dried thyme
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Fresh parsley for garnish
        Instructions:
        Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F).
        Place the potato wedges in a large bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with minced garlic, paprika, dried thyme, salt, and black pepper. Toss until the potatoes are evenly coated with the seasonings.
        Arrange the seasoned potato wedges on a baking sheet in a single layer. Bake in the preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until golden brown and crispy, flipping halfway through cooking.
        While the potatoes are baking, prepare the chicken breasts. Season both sides of the chicken breasts with salt and black pepper.
        Heat a grill pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Add a bit of olive oil to the pan.
        Once the pan is hot, add the chicken breasts. Cook for about 6-8 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and golden brown on the outside. The internal temperature of the chicken should reach 75°C (165°F).
        Remove the chicken breasts from the pan and let them rest for a few minutes before serving.
        Serve the chicken steak with the crispy potato wedges. Garnish with fresh parsley if desired. Enjoy your flavorful and satisfying chicken steak with potatoes!`,
    "cooked carrot": `Ingredients:
        4 large carrots, peeled and sliced into rounds or sticks
        2 tbsp butter or olive oil
        2 tbsp honey or brown sugar (optional)
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Chopped fresh parsley for garnish (optional)
        Instructions:
        In a large skillet or saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
        Add the sliced carrots to the skillet and toss to coat them in the butter.
        Cook the carrots for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they start to soften.
        If using honey or brown sugar, drizzle it over the carrots and toss to coat.
        Continue cooking the carrots for another 5-10 minutes, or until they are tender but still slightly crisp.
        Season the carrots with salt and black pepper to taste. Adjust seasoning if necessary.
        Remove the cooked carrots from the heat and transfer them to a serving dish.
        Garnish with chopped fresh parsley if desired, and serve hot as a delicious side dish. Enjoy your cooked carrots!`,
    "gyros chicken": `Ingredients:
        500g boneless, skinless chicken thighs, thinly sliced
        2 tbsp Greek yogurt
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        1 tsp dried oregano
        1 tsp dried thyme
        1 tsp paprika
        1/2 tsp ground cumin
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        2 tbsp olive oil
        Instructions:
        In a bowl, combine Greek yogurt, minced garlic, dried oregano, dried thyme, paprika, ground cumin, salt, and black pepper. Mix well to combine.
        Add the thinly sliced chicken thighs to the marinade and toss until evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or overnight for best results.
        Heat olive oil in a large skillet or grill pan over medium-high heat.
        Once the pan is hot, add the marinated chicken thighs in a single layer. Cook for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until the chicken is cooked through and golden brown on the outside.
        Remove the cooked chicken from the pan and let it rest for a few minutes.
        Slice the cooked chicken into thin strips.
        Serve the gyros chicken with warm pita bread, tzatziki sauce, sliced tomatoes, onions, and lettuce for a delicious gyro sandwich. Alternatively, serve over rice or salad. Enjoy your flavorful gyros chicken!`,
