        Marinate the shrimp: In a bowl, toss the shrimp with soy sauce and a splash of rice vinegar. Let it marinate for 15-20 minutes.
        Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the marinated shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until pink and cooked through.
        Assemble the poke bowl: Divide the cooked sushi rice among serving bowls. Arrange the cooked shrimp, sliced avocado, cucumber, julienned carrot, and edamame beans on top of the rice.
        Drizzle with soy sauce and sriracha mayo (if using).
        Garnish with shredded nori and sesame seeds.
