    "svíčková with brusinky":  `Ingredients:
        600g beef sirloin or tenderloin
        2 onions, chopped
        2 carrots, chopped
        2 celery stalks, chopped
        2 cloves garlic, minced
        2 bay leaves
        5 whole allspice berries
        5 whole black peppercorns
        2 cups beef broth
        1 cup heavy cream
        2 tbsp all-purpose flour
        2 tbsp unsalted butter
        1 tbsp vegetable oil
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        1/4 cup cranberry sauce (brusinky)
        Cooked bread dumplings or pasta for serving
        Instructions:
        Season the beef sirloin with salt and black pepper.
        In a large pot, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Sear the beef sirloin on all sides until browned. Remove the beef from the pot and set aside.
        In the same pot, add butter and sauté onions, carrots, celery, and garlic until softened.
        Return the beef to the pot. Add bay leaves, allspice berries, black peppercorns, and beef broth. Bring to a simmer, then cover and cook over low heat for 2-3 hours, or until the beef is tender.
        Once the beef is cooked, remove it from the pot and let it rest. Strain the cooking liquid and reserve.
        In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Whisk in flour to create a roux. Cook for 2-3 minutes.
        Gradually whisk in the reserved cooking liquid until smooth. Stir in heavy cream and simmer until the sauce thickens.
        Slice the cooked beef and serve with bread dumplings or pasta. Pour the creamy sauce over the beef.
        Garnish with cranberry sauce (brusinky) and serve hot. Enjoy your Svíčková with Brusinky!`,
    "řízek with potato salad":  `Ingredients for Řízek (Breaded Pork Cutlet):
        4 pork loin chops, boneless
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        1 cup all-purpose flour
        2 large eggs, beaten
        1 cup breadcrumbs
        Vegetable oil for frying
        Ingredients for Potato Salad:
        4 large potatoes, peeled and diced
        2 carrots, peeled and diced
        1/2 cup frozen peas
        1/4 cup mayonnaise
        2 tbsp sour cream
        1 tbsp Dijon mustard
        1 tbsp white vinegar
        Salt and black pepper to taste
        Chopped fresh parsley for garnish
        Instructions:
        Season the pork loin chops with salt and black pepper.
        Set up a breading station with three shallow dishes: one with flour, one with beaten eggs, and one with breadcrumbs.
        Dredge each pork loin chop in flour, then dip into beaten eggs, and finally coat with breadcrumbs, pressing gently to adhere.
        Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Fry the breaded pork loin chops for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and cooked through. Remove from the skillet and drain on paper towels.
        Meanwhile, cook the diced potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender. Add frozen peas during the last few minutes of cooking. Drain and let cool slightly.
        In a large bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, sour cream, Dijon mustard, and white vinegar to make the dressing.
        Add the cooked potatoes, carrots, and peas to the bowl with the dressing. Toss until well coated. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
