    "muffin":  `Ingredients:
        2 cups all-purpose flour
        1/2 cup granulated sugar
        2 tsp baking powder
        1/2 tsp baking soda
        1/2 tsp salt
        1 cup milk
        1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted
        2 large eggs
        1 tsp vanilla extract
        Optional add-ins: chocolate chips, blueberries, nuts, etc.
        Instructions:
        Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a muffin tin with paper liners or grease the cups.
        In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
        In another bowl, mix together milk, melted butter, eggs, and vanilla extract.
        Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Do not overmix.
        If using any add-ins, gently fold them into the batter.
        Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin tin, filling each cup about 3/4 full.
        Bake in the preheated oven for 18-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
        Remove the muffins from the oven and let them cool in the tin for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.
        Enjoy your delicious homemade muffins for breakfast or as a snack!`,
