        1 1/2 cups crushed chocolate cookies
        1/4 cup melted butter
        Ingredients for Cheesecake Filling:
        16 oz cream cheese, softened
        1/2 cup granulated sugar
        2 large eggs
        1 tsp vanilla extract
        1/2 cup caramel sauce
        1/2 cup chopped Twix bars (about 4 bars)
        Ingredients for Topping:
        1/2 cup chocolate chips
        1/4 cup heavy cream
        Additional chopped Twix bars for garnish
        Instructions:
        Preheat your oven to 325°F (160°C). Grease a 9-inch springform pan.
        In a bowl, mix together crushed chocolate cookies and melted butter until well combined. Press the mixture firmly into the bottom of the prepared springform pan.
        In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and granulated sugar until smooth and creamy.
        Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract.
        Pour half of the cheesecake batter over the crust in the springform pan. Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over the batter and sprinkle half of the chopped Twix bars.
        Pour the remaining cheesecake batter over the caramel and Twix layer. Drizzle the remaining caramel sauce over the batter and sprinkle the remaining chopped Twix bars.
        Bake in the preheated oven for 45-50 minutes, or until the center is almost set.
        Remove the cheesecake from the oven and let it cool in the pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Then run a knife around the edges to loosen the cheesecake from the pan. Let it cool completely.
        In a small saucepan, heat chocolate chips and heavy cream over low heat, stirring until smooth and creamy. Pour the chocolate ganache over the cooled cheesecake.
        Chill the cheesecake in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours, or until set.
        Before serving, garnish with additional chopped Twix bars if desired.
        Slice and serve your decadent Twix Cheesecake. Enjoy!`,
