    "mint and chocolate chip ice cream": `Ingredients:
        2 cups heavy cream
        1 cup whole milk
        3/4 cup granulated sugar
        1/4 cup fresh mint leaves, chopped
        1/2 tsp peppermint extract
        Green food coloring (optional)
        1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips
        Instructions:
        In a saucepan, combine heavy cream, whole milk, granulated sugar, and chopped mint leaves.
        Heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until it just begins to simmer. Do not boil.
        Remove the saucepan from the heat and let the mixture steep for about 30 minutes to infuse the mint flavor.
        Strain the mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a clean bowl, pressing on the mint leaves to extract maximum flavor. Discard the mint leaves.
        Stir in peppermint extract and green food coloring, if using, until desired color is achieved.
        Cover the bowl and refrigerate the mixture until completely chilled, preferably overnight.
        Once chilled, churn the mixture in an ice cream maker according to the manufacturer's instructions.
        During the last few minutes of churning, add the semisweet chocolate chips and continue churning until evenly distributed.
        Transfer the churned ice cream to a freezer-safe container and freeze until firm, typically 4-6 hours or overnight.
        Serve scoops of mint and chocolate chip ice cream in bowls or cones, and enjoy the refreshing and indulgent treat!`,
