        Take a small portion of the risotto mixture in your hand and flatten it to form a small disc.
        Place a cube of mozzarella cheese in the center of the disc and carefully wrap the risotto around it, forming a ball. Repeat with the remaining risotto and mozzarella cubes.
        Dip each risotto ball into the beaten eggs, then roll it in the breadcrumbs until evenly coated. Place the coated balls on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
        Heat vegetable oil in a deep fryer or large pot to 350°F (175°C).
        Carefully add the coated risotto balls to the hot oil in batches, frying until golden brown and crispy, about 3-4 minutes per batch. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
        Serve the arancini hot with marinara sauce for dipping.
        Enjoy the crispy, cheesy goodness of homemade Arancini as a delicious appetizer or snack!`,
