        Fish sauce dressing (Nuoc Cham):
        1/4 cup fish sauce
        1/4 cup water
        2 tbsp lime juice
        2 tbsp rice vinegar
        2 tbsp sugar
        1 garlic clove, minced
        1 Thai chili, thinly sliced
        Instructions:
        Cook the rice vermicelli noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking process. Set aside.
        In a bowl, mix together the soy sauce, minced garlic, brown sugar, and fish sauce. Add the thinly sliced pork and marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to overnight in the refrigerator.
        Heat the vegetable oil in a skillet or grill pan over medium-high heat. Cook the marinated pork slices for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and caramelized. Remove from heat and set aside.
        To make the fish sauce dressing (Nuoc Cham), combine fish sauce, water, lime juice, rice vinegar, sugar, minced garlic, and sliced Thai chili in a bowl. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.
        To assemble the Bun Bonambo bowls, divide the cooked rice vermicelli noodles among serving bowls. Top with shredded lettuce, bean sprouts, julienned cucumber, julienned carrot, and chopped fresh herbs.
        Arrange the cooked pork slices on top of the noodles and vegetables.
        Drizzle the fish sauce dressing over the bowls, garnish with crushed peanuts (if using), and serve with lime wedges on the side.
        Enjoy Bun Bonambo as a refreshing and flavorful Vietnamese noodle dish!`,
